## Key Concepts
- **Federated Learning**: Tenants compute updates locally; only aggregates travel upstream
- **Incremental PCA**: Streaming SVD (Oja/CCIPCA) updates components without full reprocessing
- **Missing Data Handling**: Local imputation (forward-fill, interpolation, or k-NN) before update computation
- **Differential Privacy**: Add calibrated Gaussian/Laplace noise to shared statistics; apply privacy budget (ε, δ)
- **Drift Detection**: Monitor eigenvalue stability and loading vector cosine similarity over sliding windows; trigger recomputation if divergence exceeds threshold
- **Cross-Tenant Variance**: Weight component updates by tenant sample volume; detect outlier tenants via Mahalanobis distance on loadings

## Code Example
```javascript
// Federated PCA update (streaming Oja's rule)
class FederatedPCATenant {
  constructor(nFeatures, nComponents, privacyEpsilon) {
    this.W = torch.randn(nFeatures, nComponents) * 0.1;
    this.privacyEpsilon = privacyEpsilon;
  }

  impute(data) {
    return data.fillNaN(method='forward');
  }

  localUpdate(batch) {
    const clean = this.impute(batch);
    const z = clean @ this.W;
    const gradient = (clean.T @ z - z.T @ z @ this.W) / batch.shape[0];
    this.W += this.learningRate * gradient;
    return this.computeSufficientStatistic(clean);
  }

  computeSufficientStatistic(clean) {
    const cov = clean.T @ clean / clean.shape[0];
    const noisyCov = cov + gaussianNoise(cov.shape, this.privacyEpsilon);
    return { cov: noisyCov, count: clean.shape[0] };
  }
}

class CentralAggregator {
  merge(statsList) {
    const totalCount = statsList.reduce((s, x) => s + x.count, 0);
    const mergedCov = statsList.reduce((sum, x) => 
      sum + x.cov * x.count, 0) / totalCount;
    return this.eigenDecompose(mergedCov);
  }
}
```

